<main class="container py-4 py-md-5 mt-5 page">
    <div class="card shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body p-4 p-md-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Return & Refund Policy</h1>
        <p class="muted">
          This Return & Refund Policy explains how returns, exchanges, and refunds are handled for purchases made from
          <strong>Rorito</strong> via <a href="https://www.rorito.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.rorito.com</a> or authorized Rorito channels. By placing an order, you agree to this policy.
        </p>

        <section class="section" id="window">
          <h5>Return window</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Eligible items may be returned within <strong>30 days</strong> of delivery.</li>
            <li>Items must be unused, in their original packaging, and include all accessories/manuals.</li>
            <li>Proof of purchase (order number or receipt) is required.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="eligibility">
          <h5>Eligibility and condition</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Products damaged through misuse, wear and tear, or not in resalable condition may be denied.</li>
            <li>Bundles/kits must be returned in full to qualify.</li>
            <li>Gift cards and downloadable software are non‑returnable.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="nonreturnable">
          <h5>Non‑returnable items</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>Personalized or custom-engraved items</li>
            <li>Opened consumables (e.g., inks/refills) unless defective on arrival</li>
            <li>Final sale or clearance items marked “non‑returnable”</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="process">
          <h5>How to start a return</h5>
          <ol>
            <li>Email <a href="mailto:returns@rorito.com">returns@rorito.com</a> within the return window with your order number, item, and reason.</li>
            <li>We’ll provide a Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) and instructions.</li>
            <li>Pack items securely and include the RMA inside the box. Ship by the date indicated.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="shipping">
          <h5>Return shipping</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>If the return is due to a Rorito error or a defective item, we provide a prepaid label.</li>
            <li>For preference-based returns, shipping is the customer’s responsibility and non‑refundable.</li>
            <li>Use a trackable service; Rorito isn’t responsible for returns lost in transit.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="refunds">
          <h5>Refunds</h5>
          <ul>
            <li>After inspection, approved refunds are issued to the original payment method within 5–10 business days.</li>
            <li>Original shipping fees are non‑refundable unless the return is due to our error.</li>
            <li>Partial refunds may apply for missing parts, damaged packaging, or signs of use.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="exchanges">
          <h5>Exchanges</h5>
          <p>
            For faster service, place a new order and return the original item following the process above. Exchanges are subject to stock availability.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="defective">
          <h5>Damaged or defective on arrival</h5>
          <p>
            If your Rorito product arrives damaged or defective, contact us within <strong>7 days</strong> of delivery with photos and your order number. We will arrange a replacement or refund as applicable.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="warranty">
          <h5>Warranty support</h5>
          <p>
            Some Rorito products include a limited warranty. Warranty claims may follow a different process than returns. Please refer to the product documentation or contact our team for assistance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="thirdparty">
          <h5>Purchases from other retailers</h5>
          <p>
            If you purchased a Rorito product from a third‑party retailer or marketplace, please follow their return policy. We may assist with warranty issues where applicable.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="contact">
          <h5>Contact Rorito</h5>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li>Email: <a href="mailto:returns@rorito.com">returns@rorito.com</a></li>
            <li>Support: <a href="mailto:support@rorito.com">support@rorito.com</a></li>
            <li>Address: Rorito, 123 Example St, Example City, EX 10000</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="muted mt-3 mb-0">Last updated: September 29, 2025</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

